race.comment: I'M A DEXSTAR (2) started favourite last time over 1750m at this track but could only manage second when he was prominent throughout. Won't be bothered by this longer journey and is at peak fitness now. Clearly the one to beat. EXCELMAN (1) settled well back and never threatened when beaten at Gawler. Won't find this anywhere near as tough and will relish the rise in trip. Can bounce back sharply. SIR LORD (4) chased in vain behind I'M A DEXSTAR last time but did beat him here two back. Draws well again and is an obvious threat. SUPER VALENTINE (8) comes through the same race, beating home SIR LORD. Is open to further improvement and is in the mix. RAZELLA (7) knocked off a CL1 in fine style here two weeks ago. Has more to offer but will need some luck from the wide draw.
